/TOPIC" Wounds "/

These are the effects of physical trauma, and are thus fundamentally non-magical in nature. They include broken bones, severed limbs, and other similar injuries. Instead 
of attempting to produce a long list of medical horrors only a few generalized injuries should suffice, with the GM providing any needed additional details of the specific 
wound if need be. These are treated using the healing knack, survival might also be relevant.

Note that all wounds should be treated as being of the level of the creature or effect which created the wound, or the current level of the PC suffering the wound in cases
where it is not clear what level to use.
/FLEXROW
/FLEXCELL
