The victim of this curse will /REF Shape Change REF/ into the form of a predatory beast under certain conditions. The exact conditions will depend on the type of Therianthropy
the victim is afflicted with, but the conditions listed above are appropriate for the most well-known version of the curse, lycanthropy, in which the victim transforms into
a wolf. As a rule, transformation takes approximately 5 minutes, during which time the character has all the traits associated with the animal form.

This terrible curse is said to have been originally inflicted by the Moon God Alegast on men of an ancient tribe of Erithnoi after the elves they were warring against prayed
for divine intervention. Even Alegast did not anticipate that this curse would spread and persist down the ages, bringing suffering to many humans over the generations.
Nor did he anticipate that it might spread to other races and take peculiar forms amongst them.

Beyond the curse of Alegast legends also tell of various similar curses which have afflicted individuals or groups of people at different times. The truth of these various
stories is difficult to determine at best. Each form of Therianthropy has its own slightly different attributes which may take the form of different specific curses. The
general form described here can be used as a basis for others. Many forms may exist.

Each stage of affliction progressively decreases the victim's control and human identity until in the final stage the victim becomes wholely a monstrous animalistic
shape-changer. Whenever the conditions come about which require the victim to change, a wisdom ability check is required. Success indicates the victim resists the change and
acquires one success, while failure indicates that the victim undergoes the change. If the victim then subsequently hunts and kills another human, their curse advances to the
next stage, otherwise it remains at the current stage. Once the final stage is reached, the victim's soul and personality are lost. Only the mightiest of magics is then
capable of curing the victim.
AFFLICTIONDESCRIPTION/
/CURE
Each type of therianthrope is somewhat different. In general, resistance to the changes is the best hope, and being restrained from carrying out any kills will halt the
progress of the curse in the meantime. As with other curses, rituals of purification and such, programs of fasting and prayer, etc. may also produce successes, leading to a
lifting of the curse. 
CURE/
