This poison is found in the form of seeds, flowers, bark or other plant material, or rarely a white powder refined from certain plants. Often it is prepared in the form of a
tea or infusion. While this is a fairly simple poison, and the plants it is prepared from are both reasonably common and well-known, it is rarely used due to having an extremely
bitter taste which cannot be masked. A lethal dosage is also large enough that it isn't very easy to administer without the victim's knowledge. That being said, the poison is
potent and usually lethal, and is relatively fast acting for a natural poison. As such it is fairly popular as an execution method, though death is said to be quite painful.

The check interval is about 15 minutes and checks are made against Survival.
AFFLICTIONDESCRIPTION/
/CURE
There are fairly well-known antidotes to this poison, though they are not as easily prepared, nor are the ingredients quite as available as those of the poison itself. The
best course of action is essentially just to employ Healing checks of an expert healer to keep the victim alive until they remove the poison from their system. Once a character
has succeeded in beating the affliction they will recover after a Recovery.
