This poison is greatly feared due to the extreme pain it causes. It can be permanently incapacitating and its effects are difficult to get rid of. The only saving grace is that
the antidote is more easily obtained than the substance itself, and thus if on can hang on long enough to find treatment the victim is likely to survive.

Red Agony is a blood poison, and must be administered through a would of some sort. Ingesting it or simply coming into contact with it is not enough to cause an ill effect.
It takes the form of a rust-colored liquid or paste. It is almost always applied to weapons such as darts or daggers, or in traps, where it is reputed to retain its potency
for long periods of time.

Red Agony is made via a mystical brewing process and requires several moderately rare and unusual components. It also requires the recitation of a magical ritual invoking 
certain diabolical figures.

The check period for Red Agony is 1 day, thus it may take quite a long time to kill, and the check is a Perception check.
