This is a fast-acting poison produced by alchemy. It consists of either a dark blue liquid or a white powder. In liquid form it can be slipped into food or drink.
The powder can be dissolved in liquid or ground fine and made airborne. When breathed it has a particularly quick effect.

Blue Death is well-known as one of the fastest-acting poisons known. If a victim gets a small dose they might survive for an hour. A larger dose, and especially if breathed in,
will result in almost immediate incapacitation and death.
AFFLICTIONDESCRIPTION/
/CURE
As a magically produced poison, natural antidotes are largely ineffective against this virulent poison. If it is not treated with some form of curative magic or similar
then the victim is almost sure to die. In fact normal persons of most species have virtually no chance of survival without magic. Heroes of course may survive letting the
poison run its course with a check frequency of either 30 minutes if ingested, or 1 round if inhaled.
