/AFFLICTIONDESCRIPTION
This foul brew drives its victims mad instead of killing them, which might be more merciful. Only the very stoutest of heroes can survive being subjected to Green Madness. 
Luckily it is a very rare poison. Green Madness can be administered as a contact poison, or ingested. It is infamously dangerous to use, as there are several stories of would-be assassins falling victim to
their own poison through carelessness or mischance. Even a tiny exposure runs the risk of terrible consequences.

The first 3 stages of the affliction occur quickly, with checks being made every turn. Once Stage 2 is reached then the victim becomes mad and remains in this condition for a
variable period of time depending on the dosage and the character's constitution. The final stage will not manifest for at least 3 days, but in some cases characters have
remained in this stage for up to 2 weeks. Eventually the madness becomes complete and the victim permanently loses their mind.
AFFLICTIONDESCRIPTION/
/CURE
Unfortunately the only known antidote must be prepared at the High Altar of Sawk, and is difficult to keep. Effectively one must bring a
victim to the altar, or be able to travel quickly, in order to affect a cure. 
